title: [SPOILERS] - Dagger name quip
body:
I attempted to post about daggers in general moving into season 8 but for some reason the Mod’s won’t put it up despite not telling me anything about it so I will just put this up.

Some of you may have had a read at my attempt to link Bran to the God’s of Planetos, well basically what set me off on that was the way in which Bran gave Arya Catspaw, Bran has become inhuman and his actions now all seem to be solely focused on the Night King. So I assumed that him giving Arya Catspaw was necessary, so that means she must need to have Valyrian steel which signifies to me that she will have a big role to play in the end game or at least the Night King’s endgame. So I think that Bran spoke to Jaqen posing as the Many Faced God, he told him to find Arya, get her to Essos, train her and then let her ‘escape’. It would tie up the whole plot nicely in my opinion and destroy the gaping plot holes that are there.

Then in a show/book that loves to foreshadow shit I realised the name of the dagger is CATSPAW or CAT’S PAW. For those of you who have read the books you will be familiar with Cat of the Canals, so Cat’s Paw is like saying Arya’s weapon in a way.



Source: https://ift.tt/2IBCsfY
